One of those work weeks I will always remember.

Our final report from California for the evening news has in it a few of the good and brave people we met in Altadena. 

Julian, who is more concerned about his wife than the home they no longer have; Henry R. Jones II @henryrjonesii, who rushed back to his childhood community to do everything he could to help; and Rosa, working tirelessly with a list of 110+ families, trying to provide them with what they need. Food, clothes, bags and toys. 

Seven days with a lot of grief and sadness. But also a week filled with a great amount of kindness, in the midst of the most horrible disaster.

